00:35:08.880 --> 00:35:12.300
this was all confirmed
and visualized.

00:35:12.300 --> 00:35:17.080
But also, around the time that
Thomson was discovering the

00:35:17.080 --> 00:35:19.710
electron, there were some other
observations that were

00:35:19.710 --> 00:35:23.740
going on, and the most
disturbing to kind of the

00:35:23.740 --> 00:35:26.500
understanding of the universe
was the fact that there were

00:35:26.500 --> 00:35:29.590
some observations about light
that didn't make sense with

00:35:29.590 --> 00:35:32.600
this idea that light
is a particle.

00:35:32.600 --> 00:35:35.720
And the photoelectric effect
is maybe the most clear

00:35:35.720 --> 00:35:37.320
example of this.

00:35:37.320 --> 00:35:41.180
So, the photoelectric effect is
the effect that if you have

00:35:41.180 --> 00:35:43.550
some metal, and you can pick
essentially any metal you

00:35:43.550 --> 00:35:47.380
want, and you shine light of a
certain frequency onto that

00:35:47.380 --> 00:35:52.110
metal, you can actually pop off
an electron, and you can

00:35:52.110 --> 00:35:54.110
go ahead and measure what the
kinetic energy of that

00:35:54.110 --> 00:35:57.110
electron that comes off is,
because we can measure the

00:35:57.110 --> 00:36:00.530
velocity and we know that
kinetic energy equals 1/2 m b

00:36:00.530 --> 00:36:02.720
squared, and thanks to
Thomson we also know

00:36:02.720 --> 00:36:05.150
the mass of an electron.

00:36:05.150 --> 00:36:09.140
So, this is an interesting
observation, and in itself not

00:36:09.140 --> 00:36:13.790
too disturbing, yet but the
important thing to point out

00:36:13.790 --> 00:36:18.170
is that there's this threshold
frequency that is of the

00:36:18.170 --> 00:36:20.360
metal, and each metal has a
different threshold frequency,

00:36:20.360 --> 00:36:23.680
such as if you shine light on
the metal where the frequency

00:36:23.680 --> 00:36:27.680
of the light is less than the
threshold frequency, nothing

00:36:27.680 --> 00:36:31.900
will happen -- no electron will
pop off of that metal.

00:36:31.900 --> 00:36:34.450
However, if you shine a light
with a frequency that's

00:36:34.450 --> 00:36:37.470
greater than the threshold
frequency, you will be able to

00:36:37.470 --> 00:36:39.320
pop off an electron.

00:36:39.320 --> 00:36:42.080
So, people were making this
observation, but this wasn't

00:36:42.080 --> 00:36:44.570
making any sense at all because
there was nothing in

00:36:44.570 --> 00:36:46.890
classical physics that
described any sort of

00:36:46.890 --> 00:36:51.510
relationship between the
frequency of light and the

00:36:51.510 --> 00:36:55.310
energy, much less the energy of
an electron that would get

00:36:55.310 --> 00:37:01.030
popped off of a metal that would
basically come off only

00:37:01.030 --> 00:37:03.820
when we're hitting this
threshold frequency.

00:37:03.820 --> 00:37:07.050
So, what they could do was
actually graph what was

00:37:07.050 --> 00:37:10.050
happening here, so we can also
graph what was happening, and

00:37:10.050 --> 00:37:13.590
what they found was that if we
were at any point below the

00:37:13.590 --> 00:37:16.460
threshold frequency and we were
counting the numbers of

00:37:16.460 --> 00:37:20.000
electrons that were popping off
of our metal, we weren't

00:37:20.000 --> 00:37:21.810
seeing anything at all.

00:37:21.810 --> 00:37:25.650
But if you go up the threshold
frequency, suddenly you see

00:37:25.650 --> 00:37:28.420
that there's some number of
electrons that comes off, and

00:37:28.420 --> 00:37:31.110
amazingly, the number of
electrons actually had no

00:37:31.110 --> 00:37:35.240
relationship at all to the
frequency of the light.

00:37:35.240 --> 00:37:38.040
And this didn't make a lot of
sense to people at the time

00:37:38.040 --> 00:37:42.710
because they thought that the
frequency should be related to

00:37:42.710 --> 00:37:44.880
the number of electrons that
are coming off, because you

00:37:44.880 --> 00:37:48.340
have more frequency coming in,
you'd expect more electrons

00:37:48.340 --> 00:37:49.510
that are coming off
-- this wasn't

00:37:49.510 --> 00:37:50.860
what people were seeing.

00:37:50.860 --> 00:37:53.270
So, what they decided to do
is just study absolutely

00:37:53.270 --> 00:37:56.100
everything they could about the
photoelectric effect and

00:37:56.100 --> 00:37:58.300
hope, at some point, someone
would piece something together

00:37:58.300 --> 00:38:00.660
that could explain what's going
on or shed some light on

00:38:00.660 --> 00:38:02.440
this effect.

00:38:02.440 --> 00:38:04.620
So, one thing they did, because
it was so easy to

00:38:04.620 --> 00:38:08.630
measure kinetic energy of
electrons, is plot the

00:38:08.630 --> 00:38:11.600
frequency of the light against
the kinetic energy of the

00:38:11.600 --> 00:38:13.860
electron that's coming
off here.

00:38:13.860 --> 00:38:16.040
And in your notes and on these
slides here, just for your

00:38:16.040 --> 00:38:18.090
reference, I'm just pointing
out what's going to be

00:38:18.090 --> 00:38:19.930
predicted from classical
physics.

00:38:19.930 --> 00:38:22.060
You're not responsible for
that and we won't really

00:38:22.060 --> 00:38:24.290
discuss it, but it just gives
you the contrast of the

00:38:24.290 --> 00:38:26.700
surprise that comes up when
people make these

00:38:26.700 --> 00:38:27.840
observations.

00:38:27.840 --> 00:38:30.800
And the first observation was
that the frequency of the

00:38:30.800 --> 00:38:34.190
light had a linear relationship
to the kinetic

00:38:34.190 --> 00:38:38.620
energy of the electrons
that are ejected here.

00:38:38.620 --> 00:38:42.040
This made no sense at all to
people, and again they saw

00:38:42.040 --> 00:38:44.620
this effect where if you were
below that threshold

00:38:44.620 --> 00:38:48.900
frequency, you saw
nothing at all.

00:38:48.900 --> 00:38:51.800
So, that was frequency
with kinetic energy.

00:38:51.800 --> 00:38:54.350
The next thing that they wanted
to look at was the

00:38:54.350 --> 00:38:57.870
actual intensity of the light
and see what the relationship

00:38:57.870 --> 00:39:00.610
of intensity to kinetic
energy is.

00:39:00.610 --> 00:39:03.640
So, what we would expect is that
there is a relationship

00:39:03.640 --> 00:39:06.380
between intensity in kinetic
energy, because it was

00:39:06.380 --> 00:39:08.790
understood that however intense
the light was, if you

00:39:08.790 --> 00:39:10.810
had a more intense light,
it was a higher

00:39:10.810 --> 00:39:12.270
energy light beam.

00:39:12.270 --> 00:39:14.940
So that should mean that the
energy that's transferred to

00:39:14.940 --> 00:39:18.000
the electron should be greater,
but that's not what

00:39:18.000 --> 00:39:20.830
you saw at all, and what you
saw is that if you kept the

00:39:20.830 --> 00:39:25.390
frequency constant, there was
absolutely no change in the

00:39:25.390 --> 00:39:28.490
kinetic energy of the electrons,
no matter how high

00:39:28.490 --> 00:39:30.980
up you had the intensity
of the light go.

00:39:30.980 --> 00:39:33.650
You could keep increasing the
intensity and nothing was

00:39:33.650 --> 00:39:36.790
going to happen.

00:39:36.790 --> 00:39:40.040
So, we could also plot the
number of electrons that are

00:39:40.040 --> 00:39:43.930
ejected as a relationship to the
intensity, so that was yet

00:39:43.930 --> 00:39:46.330
another experiment
they could do.

00:39:46.330 --> 00:39:48.790
And this is what they had
expected that there would be

00:39:48.790 --> 00:39:53.380
no relationship, but instead
here they saw that there was a

00:39:53.380 --> 00:39:56.820
linear relationship not to the
intensity and the kinetic

00:39:56.820 --> 00:39:59.340
energy of the electrons, but
to the intensity and the

00:39:59.340 --> 00:40:00.610
number of electrons.

00:40:00.610 --> 00:40:03.920
So, none of these observations
made sense to any scientists

00:40:03.920 --> 00:40:06.780
at the time, and really all of
these observations were made

00:40:06.780 --> 00:40:10.040
and somewhat put aside for
several years before someone

00:40:10.040 --> 00:40:12.970
that could kind of process
everything that was going on

00:40:12.970 --> 00:40:17.620
at once came along, and that
person was Einstein,

00:40:17.620 --> 00:40:19.930
conveniently enough -- if anyone
could put it together,

00:40:19.930 --> 00:40:22.730
we would hope that he
could, and he did.

00:40:22.730 --> 00:40:26.340
And what he did in a way that
made sense when all of us look

00:40:26.340 --> 00:40:30.190
at it, is he plotted all of
these different metals on the

00:40:30.190 --> 00:40:32.310
same graph and made
some observations.

00:40:32.310 --> 00:40:35.760
So, for example, here we're
showing rubidium and potassium

00:40:35.760 --> 00:40:40.190
and sodium plotted where we're
plotting the frequency --

00:40:40.190 --> 00:40:43.920
that's the frequency of that
light that's coming into the

00:40:43.920 --> 00:40:47.820
metal versus the kinetic energy
of the electron that's

00:40:47.820 --> 00:40:50.980
ejected from the surface
of the metal.

00:40:50.980 --> 00:40:53.980
And what he found here, which is
what you can see and we can

00:40:53.980 --> 00:40:57.390
all see pretty clearly, is the
slope of all of these lines is

00:40:57.390 --> 00:41:01.040
the same regardless of what
the type of metal is.

00:41:01.040 --> 00:41:05.270
So, he fit all these to the
equation of the line, and what

00:41:05.270 --> 00:41:08.000
he noticed was the slope was
specifically this number,

00:41:08.000 --> 00:41:13.530
6.626 times 10 to the negative
34, joules times seconds.

00:41:13.530 --> 00:41:18.290
And he also found that the y
intercept for each one of

00:41:18.290 --> 00:41:23.990
these metals was equal to
basically this number here,

00:41:23.990 --> 00:41:31.820
which was the slope times the
minimum frequency required of

00:41:31.820 --> 00:41:37.160
each specific metal, so that's
of the threshold frequency.

00:41:37.160 --> 00:41:40.960
And he actually knew that this
number had popped up before,

00:41:40.960 --> 00:41:44.070
and a lot of you are familiar
with this number also, and

00:41:44.070 --> 00:41:45.620
this is Planck's constant.

00:41:45.620 --> 00:41:48.440
Planck had observed this number
as a fitting constant

00:41:48.440 --> 00:41:51.060
years earlier when he looked at
some phenomena, and you can

00:41:51.060 --> 00:41:53.810
read about in your book, such
as black body radiation.

00:41:53.810 --> 00:41:57.680
And what he found was he needed
this constant to fit

00:41:57.680 --> 00:42:00.210
his data to what was observed.

00:42:00.210 --> 00:42:02.700
And this is the same thing that
Einstein was observing,

00:42:02.700 --> 00:42:07.170
that he needed this fitting
constant, that this constant

00:42:07.170 --> 00:42:09.360
was just falling right out of,
for example, this slope and

00:42:09.360 --> 00:42:11.110
also the y intercept.

00:42:11.110 --> 00:42:15.720
So he decided to go ahead and
define exactly what it is,

00:42:15.720 --> 00:42:19.760
this line, in terms of these new
constants, this constant

00:42:19.760 --> 00:42:22.560
he's calling h, which is
Planck's constant.

00:42:22.560 --> 00:42:25.650
So, on the y axis we have
kinetic energy, so we

00:42:25.650 --> 00:42:27.460
can plug that in.

00:42:27.460 --> 00:42:29.980
If we talk about what the x
axis is, that's just the

00:42:29.980 --> 00:42:32.200
frequency of the light
that's coming in.

00:42:32.200 --> 00:42:36.420
We know what m is,
m is equal to h.

00:42:36.420 --> 00:42:41.900
And then we can plug in what b
is, the y intercept, because

00:42:41.900 --> 00:42:45.140
that's just the negative
of h times

00:42:45.140 --> 00:42:47.090
that threshold frequency.

00:42:47.090 --> 00:42:50.520
So we have this new equation
here when we're considering

00:42:50.520 --> 00:42:53.250
this photoelectric effect,
which is that the kinetic

00:42:53.250 --> 00:42:59.180
energy is equal to h nu minus
h nu threshold of the metal.

00:42:59.180 --> 00:43:03.210
And what Einstein concluded
and observed is that well,

00:43:03.210 --> 00:43:07.160
kinetic energy, of course,
that's an energy term, and h

00:43:07.160 --> 00:43:10.170
times nu, well that has to be
energy also, because energy

00:43:10.170 --> 00:43:13.280
has to be equal to energy --
there's no other way about it.

00:43:13.280 --> 00:43:15.740
And this worked out with units
as well because we're talking

00:43:15.740 --> 00:43:18.510
about joules for kinetic energy,
and when we're talking

00:43:18.510 --> 00:43:20.880
about h times nu, we're talking
about joules times

00:43:20.880 --> 00:43:23.490
second times inverse seconds.

00:43:23.490 --> 00:43:26.320
So, the very important
conclusion that Einstein made

00:43:26.320 --> 00:43:32.000
here is that energy is equal to
h times nu, or that h times

00:43:32.000 --> 00:43:35.280
nu is an actual energy term.

00:43:35.280 --> 00:43:39.690
And this kind of went along
with two observations.

00:43:39.690 --> 00:43:41.940
The first is that energy
of a photon is

00:43:41.940 --> 00:43:43.850
proportional to its frequency.

00:43:43.850 --> 00:43:47.300
So this was never recognized
before that if we know the

00:43:47.300 --> 00:43:52.450
frequency of a photon or a wave
of light, we can know the

00:43:52.450 --> 00:43:54.230
energy of that light.

00:43:54.230 --> 00:43:57.060
So, since we know that there's
relationship also between

00:43:57.060 --> 00:43:59.560
frequency and wavelength, we can
do the same thing -- if we

00:43:59.560 --> 00:44:02.650
know the wavelength, we can know
the energy of the light.

00:44:02.650 --> 00:44:05.480
And I use the term photon here,
and that's because he

00:44:05.480 --> 00:44:08.500
also concluded that light must
be made up of these energy

00:44:08.500 --> 00:44:11.250
packets, and each packet has
that h, that Planck's

00:44:11.250 --> 00:44:15.210
constant's worth of energy in
it, so that's why you have to

00:44:15.210 --> 00:44:17.940
multiply Planck's constant
times the frequency.

00:44:17.940 --> 00:44:21.620
Any frequency can't have an
energy, you have to -- you

00:44:21.620 --> 00:44:24.900
don't have a continuum of
frequencies that are of a

00:44:24.900 --> 00:44:28.900
certain energy, it's actually
punctuated into these packets

00:44:28.900 --> 00:44:30.430
that are called photons.

00:44:30.430 --> 00:44:33.330
And, as you know, Einstein made
many, many, many very

00:44:33.330 --> 00:44:36.870
important contributions to
science and relativity, but he

00:44:36.870 --> 00:44:41.660
called this his one single most
important contribution to

00:44:41.660 --> 00:44:45.740
science, the relationship
between energy and frequency

00:44:45.740 --> 00:44:48.660
and the idea of photons.

00:44:48.660 --> 00:44:52.030
So this means we now have a new
way of thinking about the

00:44:52.030 --> 00:44:57.400
photoelectric effect, and that
is the idea that h times nu is

00:44:57.400 --> 00:44:59.130
actually an energy.

00:44:59.130 --> 00:45:02.060
So, it's the energy of an
incident photon if we're

00:45:02.060 --> 00:45:04.760
talking about nu where we're
talking about the energy of

00:45:04.760 --> 00:45:08.890
the photon going in, so we can
abbreviate that as e sub i,

00:45:08.890 --> 00:45:11.050
energy of the incident photon.

00:45:11.050 --> 00:45:16.170
We can talk about also h times
nu nought, which is that

00:45:16.170 --> 00:45:17.840
threshold frequency.

00:45:17.840 --> 00:45:20.380
So this is a term we're going
to see a lot, especially in

00:45:20.380 --> 00:45:23.620
your problem sets, it's called
the work function, and the

00:45:23.620 --> 00:45:27.410
work function is the same
thing as the threshold

00:45:27.410 --> 00:45:29.320
frequency of a metal, except,
of course, that it's

00:45:29.320 --> 00:45:31.280
multiplied by Planck's
constant.

00:45:31.280 --> 00:45:34.910
So, it's the minimum energy that
a certain metal requires

00:45:34.910 --> 00:45:36.700
in order to pop a photon out of
it -- in order to eject an

00:45:36.700 --> 00:45:38.100
electron from the surface
of that metal.

00:45:38.100 --> 00:45:46.160
So this is our new kind of
schematic way that we can

00:45:46.160 --> 00:45:50.240
think about looking at the
photoelectric effect, so if

00:45:50.240 --> 00:45:53.580
this is the total amount of
energy that we put into the

00:45:53.580 --> 00:45:57.430
system, where here we have the
energy of a free electron.

00:45:57.430 --> 00:46:01.660
We have this much energy going
in, the metal itself requires

00:46:01.660 --> 00:46:04.540
this much energy, the
work function, in

00:46:04.540 --> 00:46:06.280
order to eject an electron.

00:46:06.280 --> 00:46:08.720
So that much energy is
going to be used up

00:46:08.720 --> 00:46:09.620
just ejecting it.

00:46:09.620 --> 00:46:12.840
And what we have left over is
this amount of energy here,

00:46:12.840 --> 00:46:15.320
which is going to be
the kinetic energy

00:46:15.320 --> 00:46:17.600
of the ejected electron.

00:46:17.600 --> 00:46:20.650
So, therefore, we can rewrite
our equation in two ways.

00:46:20.650 --> 00:46:24.410
One is just talking about it in
terms only of energy where

00:46:24.410 --> 00:46:27.580
our kinetic energy here is going
to be equal to the total

00:46:27.580 --> 00:46:32.220
energy going in -- the energy
initial minus this energy of

00:46:32.220 --> 00:46:34.210
the work function here.

00:46:34.210 --> 00:46:38.880
We can also talk about it in
terms of if we want to solve,

00:46:38.880 --> 00:46:41.120
if we, for example, we want to
find out what that initial

00:46:41.120 --> 00:46:44.370
energy was, we can just
rearrange our equation, or we

00:46:44.370 --> 00:46:48.110
can look at this here where the
initial energy is equal to

00:46:48.110 --> 00:46:50.800
kinetic energy plus
the work function.

00:46:50.800 --> 00:46:54.640
So before we go we'll try to
see if we can do a clicker

00:46:54.640 --> 00:46:58.610
question for you on this,
and we can, very good.

